export const updateMeta = {
  date: '2026-07-12',
  title: 'SEO meta-description pass: keyword-first rewrites under 155 chars + trust-language fix',
  tags: ['seo', 'metadata', 'meta-description'],
};
---
<article class="border-l-4 border-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] pl-6">
  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-1">July 12, 2026</h2>
  <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-4">
    Rewrote the <code>meta description</code> on <strong>138 hand-authored core pages</strong> so each one leads
    with its primary keyword, states a benefit, and closes on a soft CTA within <strong>155 characters</strong>.
    An audit of 274 pages found 191 descriptions running past the ~160-character search-result cutoff (so they
    truncated), no duplicates, and two utility pages missing a description entirely. This pass fixes the
    hand-authored surface; the programmatic geo pages remain on the follow-up list.
  </p>

  <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-1">Pages rewritten (138)</p>
  <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-4">
    Homepage, all species pages, platform pages (<a href="/features" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">Features</a>,
    <a href="/mobile" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">Mobile</a>,
    <a href="/trust" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">Trust</a>),
    <a href="/for-breeders" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">For Breeders</a> and
    <a href="/for-breed-clubs" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">Breed Clubs</a>,
    the <a href="/buyers" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">Buyers</a> guides, every free tool and
    calculator, all <a href="/workflows" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">workflow</a> pages, the
    <a href="/compare/best-horse-breeding-software" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">comparison</a> and
    <a href="/articles" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">article</a> pages, the
    <a href="/services" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">Services</a> and
    <a href="/facilities" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">Facilities</a> category hubs, and the
    provider-acquisition pages. On the six comparison pages and the data-problem article, the matching
    JSON-LD <code>description</code> was updated in lockstep so structured data and the meta tag stay in sync.
  </p>

  <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-1">Trust-language fix (1 template)</p>
  <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-4">
    The dynamic services template at <code>/services/[category]/[state]</code> generated every un-hand-authored
    city and state page with a description reading "Verified provider profiles." That phrasing was replaced with
    "Real provider profiles" to align with the marketplace trust posture, which does not claim to verify or vouch
    for providers. This corrects the description on every programmatically generated services location page.
  </p>

  <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">
    SEO only: no on-page copy, routing, or navigation changed. Companion to the same-day
    <a href="/site-updates" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">title-tag SEO pass</a>. Every rewritten
    description now leads with the primary keyword and stays within the search-result character budget.
  </p>
</article>
